V{{Infobox economist\u000a| name              = David A. Crocker\u000a| color            = \u000a| school_tradition = \u000a| image            = \u000a| image_size       = \u000a| caption          = \u000a| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1937|10|04}}\u000a| birth_place      = \u000a| death_date       =\u000a| nick_name        = \u000a| death_place      =\u000a| nationality      = [[United States|American]]\u000a| religion         = \u000a| residence        = \u000a| alma_mater       = [[Yale University]]\u000a| field            = [[Development ethics]]\u000a| institution      = [[University of Maryland]]\u000a| influences       = \u000a| influenced       = \u000a| contributions    = \u000a| awards           = \u000a| signature        = <!--file name only-->\u000a}}\u000a'''David A. Crocker''' (born 4 October 1937),<ref name=LCCN>{{cite web|title=Crocker, David A.|url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n82011556.html|publisher=Library of Congress|accessdate=8 July 2014|quote=found: Ethics of consumption, 1997: CIP t.p. (David A. Crocker) data sheet (b. 10-04-37)}}</ref> is Senior Research Scholar in the School of Public Policy, at the [[University of Maryland]],<ref name=CV>{{cite web|title=David Crocker, vitae |url= http://www.ethicsofempowerment.org/vitae/Crocker.pdf |publisher = Ethics of empowerment |date= May 2007 |accessdate=8 July 2014}}</ref> he is also the founder and former president of the International Development Ethics Association (IDEA).<ref name=IDEA>{{cite web|title=About: History of IDEA|url=http://developmentethics.org/about-2/|website=Wordpress|publisher=IDEA: International Development Ethics Association|accessdate=8 July 2014}}</ref> His work<ref>{{Cite journal | last = Crocker | first = David A | title = Deliberative participation in local development | journal = Journal of Human Development and Capabilities &#124; Special issue: selected papers from the 2006 International Conference of the Human Development and Capability Association | volume = 8 | issue = 3 | pages = 431-455 | publisher = Taylor and Francis | doi = 10.1080/14649880701462379 | date = 2007 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1080/14649880701462379 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref> has also been cited by the [[Human Development Report|United Nations Human Development Report]].<ref>{{cite book | contribution = Chapter 1. Reaffirming human development &#124; The original statement | editor-last = United Nations Development Programme | editor-first = UNDP | editor-link = United Nations Development Programme | title = Human Development Report 2010 &#124; 20th anniversary edition &#124; the real wealth of nations: pathways to human development | page = 13 | publisher = United Nations Development Programme | location = New York, NY | year = 2010 | isbn = 9780230284456 | ref = harv | postscript = . }} [http://hdr.undp.org/sites/default/files/reports/270/hdr_2010_en_complete_reprint.pdf Pdf version.]</ref>\u000a\u000a== Education ==\u000aDavid Crocker gained his bachelor's degree in psychology from [[DePauw University]], [[Greencastle, Indiana]], in 1959. He also has three degrees from [[Yale University]] ([[Master of Divinity|M.Div]] in Philosophy of Religion 1963, [[Master's degree|MA]] in Philosophical Theology and Philosophy of Religion 1965, and a [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D]] in Philosophical Theology and Philosophy of Religion 1970).<ref name=CV />\u000a\u000a== Academic career ==\u000a* Taught philosophy for 25 years at [[Colorado State University]]<ref name=CV />\u000a* UNESCO Chair in Development at the [[University of Valencia]].<ref name=UNESCO>{{Citation | last = Morris | first = Christopher | contribution = Contributors | editor-last = Morris | editor-first = Christopher | title = Amartya Sen | pages = xi | publisher = Cambridge University Press | location = Cambridge New York | year = 2009 | isbn = 9780521618069 }}</ref>\u000a* Fellow of the [[Human Development and Capability Association]].<ref name=HDCA>{{cite web|title=HDCA fellows|url= https://hd-ca.org/about/hdca-fellows|publisher=Human Development and Capability Association|accessdate=8 July 2014}}</ref>\u000a\u000a== Media ==\u000aCrocker was one of a number of leading philosophers who, at the 1998 World Congress of Philosophy, were interviewed by [[Michael S. Malone|Michael Malone]] for the television series, ''A parliament of minds: philosophy for a new millennium''.<ref name=PBS>{{cite AV media | people = Michael S. Malone (host) Michael Tobias (dir) | title = A parliament of minds: philosophy for a new millennium (Democracy, ethics and the relevance of philosophy / David Crocker) | medium = TV Mini-Series documentary / VHS video | publisher = produced for PBS by KTEH/San Jose Public Television and JMT Productions in association with the Wisdom Channel | date = 1999 | OCLC = 48127065 }}</ref><ref name=SFSU>{{cite web | title= A Parliament of Minds: 109. David Crocker - Democracy, Ethics and the Relevancy of Philosophy |url= http://at.sfsu.edu/md5/aparliamentofminds109davidcrockerdemocracyethicsandtherelevancyofphilosophy10970 |publisher= San Francisco State University / Academic Technology | accessdate= 8 July 2014}}</ref>\u000a\u000a== Bibliography ==\u000a=== Films ===\u000a* {{cite AV media | people = Michael S. Malone (host) Michael Tobias (dir) | title = A parliament of minds: philosophy for a new millennium (Democracy, ethics and the relevance of philosophy / David Crocker) | medium = TV Mini-Series documentary / VHS video | publisher = produced for PBS by KTEH/San Jose Public Television and JMT Productions in association with the Wisdom Channel | date = 1999 | OCLC = 48127065 }} \u000a\u000a=== Books ===\u000a* {{cite book | last = Crocker | first = David | title = Ethics of global development: agency, capability, and deliberative democracy | publisher = Cambridge University Press | location = Cambridge New York | year = 2008 | isbn = 9780521885195 }}\u000a\u000a=== Chapters in books ===\u000a* {{Citation | last = 